Quote:  After the bush was cleared, Cape Gooseberries, distributed by birds, sprang up everywhere giving rise to a recipe for "Terawhiti Pie", in Betty's Old Curiosity Recipe Book, with chops in a camp oven, onions and potatoes, topped off with Cape Gooseberries; but the cattle later ate them out.
